From: aorus-5090-egpu <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 7 May 2026 19:45:00 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] G3-H — clear GPU AER UncMask at probe to match Windows behavior

Targets H17.G3 (Gen3 GSP_LOCKDOWN root cause) per task #106.

Empirical evidence (windows-test/powershell-cmds.txt 2026-05-07):
  Windows DEVPKEY_PciDevice_Uncorrectable_Error_Mask = 0
  Windows DEVPKEY_PciDevice_Correctable_Error_Mask   = 0
  Windows DEVPKEY_PciDevice_ECRC_Errors              = 160 (tolerated)

Linux observed (every probe-end since 2026-05-07):
  GPU_AER_UncMsk = 0x00400000  (bit 22 = Uncorrectable Internal Error)
  GPU_AER_Cor    = 0x00002000  (bit 13 = Advisory Non-Fatal)

Mechanism:
  PCIe r6 §6.2.3.2: when an Uncorrectable error fires AND the
  corresponding bit in the Uncorrectable Error MASK register is SET,
  the error is "downgraded" to Advisory Non-Fatal — Cor bit 13 set,
  UncStatus NOT updated, Header Log NOT captured.

  Linux PCI core (or AORUS BIOS) sets UncMask bit 22 at probe time,
  which means GPU PCIe IP-internal errors get silently demoted. We
  see Cor=0x2000 with no Uncor capture and no recovery handler trigger.

  Windows leaves UncMask=0. Internal Errors fire as Uncorrectable
  Non-Fatal (per UncSeverity which has bit 22 = Non-Fatal), routed
  through standard AER recovery flow. Windows's nvlddmkm tolerates
  these via PCIe link layer retry; ECRC errors counted but operation
  continues.

Implementation:
  In tb_egpu_lever_m_recover_init() (called from nv_pci_probe), write
  PCI_ERR_UNCOR_MASK = 0 on the GPU PCIe device. Runs BEFORE the
  NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable check, so the unmask is independent
  of the recovery state machine — even with M-recover disabled, we
  want errors visible rather than silently demoted.

  Gated by NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable (default 1). Disable via
  cmdline arg if causes regression.

Decision matrix this enables:
  - On port B (currently working at Gen3): observe whether UncMask=0
    changes [DIAG]/[DIAG-AER] pattern. If Internal Error now fires as
    Unc Non-Fatal (UncStatus bit 22 set, Header Log populated), we
    have a pcie_error_handlers hook to react.
  - On port A (currently fails 36 LOCKDOWN at Gen3): test whether
    the demotion was the cause of the cascade. If port A succeeds
    with UncMask=0, the silent demotion + lack of recovery hook was
    the proximate cause. If port A still fails, demotion was NOT
    the proximate cause.

Aligns with project scope per memory feedback_project_scope_path_a:
  full open-driver parity with Windows closed driver.

Tasks: #106
---
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.c
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.c
@@ -86,6 +86,30 @@
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMResetSettleMs,
     "AORUS Lever M-recover: settle delay (ms) after bus reset before re-checking (default 500)");
 
+/* G3-H (2026-05-07): Match Windows AER configuration.
+ *
+ * Empirical (windows-test/powershell-cmds.txt 2026-05-07):
+ *   Windows DEVPKEY_PciDevice_Uncorrectable_Error_Mask = 0
+ *
+ * Linux observed (archive/gen3-fail-2026-05-07-165158, port-A and port-B
+ * boots): GPU_AER_UncMsk = 0x00400000 (bit 22 = Uncorrectable Internal
+ * Error MASKED). When Internal Error fires, masking demotes it to
+ * Advisory Non-Fatal (Cor bit 13 = 0x00002000) — observed at every
+ * probe-end. Header Log is bypassed.
+ *
+ * Setting UncMask = 0 lets Internal Error fire as Uncorrectable Non-Fatal,
+ * which:
+ *   - Triggers standard AER recovery flow (pci_error_handlers callbacks)
+ *   - Hooks into our Lever M-recover state machine via slot_reset/resume
+ *   - Populates Header Log with the offending TLP for diagnosis
+ *
+ * Default-on. Disable via NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable=0 if it causes
+ * regressions. Task #106. */
+unsigned int NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable = 1;
+module_param(NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable, uint, 0644);
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable,
+    "AORUS G3-H: clear GPU AER UncMask at probe to match Windows (1=on default, 0=off)");
+
 /* No-op work handler stub — Commit 2 fills in the actual recovery
  * sequence. For Commit 1 we just log that the workqueue plumbing fired,
  * increment the counter, and return. Useful for sanity-checking the
@@ -425,6 +449,35 @@
     struct tb_egpu_lever_m_recover *lm;
     nv_state_t *nv = NV_STATE_PTR(nvl);
 
+    /* G3-H: clear GPU AER UncMask at probe to match Windows behavior.
+     * Runs regardless of NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable since unmasking
+     * is independent of the recovery state machine — even with M-recover
+     * disabled, we want errors visible rather than silently demoted. */
+    if (NVreg_TbEgpuUncMaskClearEnable && nvl->pci_dev)
+    {
+        struct pci_dev *pdev = nvl->pci_dev;
+        int aer_pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_ERR);
+        if (aer_pos)
+        {
+            u32 old_mask = 0;
+            (void)pci_read_config_dword(pdev, aer_pos + PCI_ERR_UNCOR_MASK, &old_mask);
+            if (old_mask != 0)
+            {
+                (void)pci_write_config_dword(pdev, aer_pos + PCI_ERR_UNCOR_MASK, 0);
+                NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_ERRORS, nv,
+                    "AORUS UncMaskClear (G3-H): GPU AER UncMask 0x%08x -> 0x00000000 "
+                    "(matching Windows; un-masks Internal Error so Unc Non-Fatal fires "
+                    "instead of Cor=0x2000 demotion)\n",
+                    old_mask);
+            }
+            else
+            {
+                NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_INFO, nv,
+                    "AORUS UncMaskClear (G3-H): GPU AER UncMask already 0x00000000; no change\n");
+            }
+        }
+    }
+
     if (!NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable)
     {
         NV_DEV_PRINTF(NV_DBG_INFO, nv,
